The paper proposes a framework for online multiagent coordination and decision making under uncertainty, which involves heuristic search and Bayesian modeling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Multiagent Systems (cs.MA), and Machine Learning (cs.LG), which are all concerned with intelligent decision making and coordination. Additionally, the paper involves robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY), as it applies the proposed framework to a smart factory case study.
